
CryptoWiki App Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 25-10-2023

1. Introduction

Welcome to CryptoWiki App! This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information. By using CryptoWiki App, you agree to the terms described herein. We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring the security of your data.

2. Information We Collect

2.1. User-Provided Information: We may collect information you provide, such as your username, email address, and any content you submit within the app.

2.2. Automatically Collected Information: We may collect data like your device type, IP address, and usage statistics for analytics and app optimization.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use your information to provide and improve CryptoWiki App, personalize your experience, send you updates, and ensure the app's functionality and security.

4. Sharing Your Information

We do not sell your information to third parties. We may share data with service providers to maintain app functionality and security.

5. Security

We employ industry-standard measures to protect your data, but no method is completely secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Your Choices

You can access, update, or delete your information within the app. You may also contact us to exercise your data rights.

7. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this policy as needed. We will notify you of changes via the app or other means.

8. Contact Us

If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at sumanmali019@gmail.com.

Please review this Privacy Policy regularly for updates. Your continued use of CryptoWiki App signifies your acceptance of these terms.
